23namespace webrtc {
24static constexpr const int kRedMaxPacketSize =
25 1 << 10; // RED packets must be less than 1024 bytes to fit the 10 bit
26 // block length.
27static constexpr const size_t kAudioMaxRtpPacketLen =
28 1200; // The typical MTU is 1200 bytes.
29
30static constexpr size_t kRedHeaderLength = 4; // 4 bytes RED header.
31static constexpr size_t kRedLastHeaderLength =
32 1; // reduced size for last RED header.
33
34static constexpr size_t kRedNumberOfRedundantEncodings =
35 2; // The level of redundancy we support.
36
37AudioEncoderCopyRed::Config::Config() = default;
38AudioEncoderCopyRed::Config::Config(Config&&) = default;
39AudioEncoderCopyRed::Config::~Config() = default;
40
41size_t GetMaxRedundancyFromFieldTrial() {
42 const std::string red_trial =
43 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-Audio-Red-For-Opus");
44 size_t redundancy = 0;
45 if (sscanf(red_trial.c_str(), "Enabled-%zu", &redundancy) != 1 ||
46 redundancy < 1 || redundancy > 9) {
47 return kRedNumberOfRedundantEncodings;
48 }
49 return redundancy;
50}
51
52AudioEncoderCopyRed::AudioEncoderCopyRed(Config&& config)
53 : speech_encoder_(std::move(config.speech_encoder)),
54 primary_encoded_(0, kAudioMaxRtpPacketLen),
55 max_packet_length_(kAudioMaxRtpPacketLen),
56 red_payload_type_(config.payload_type) {
57 RTC_CHECK(speech_encoder_) << "Speech encoder not provided.";
58
59 auto number_of_redundant_encodings = GetMaxRedundancyFromFieldTrial();
60 for (size_t i = 0; i < number_of_redundant_encodings; i++) {
61 std::pair<EncodedInfo, rtc::Buffer> redundant;
62 redundant.second.EnsureCapacity(kAudioMaxRtpPacketLen);
63 redundant_encodings_.push_front(std::move(redundant));
64 }
65}
66
67AudioEncoderCopyRed::~AudioEncoderCopyRed() = default;

93AudioEncoder::EncodedInfo AudioEncoderCopyRed::EncodeImpl(
94 uint32_t rtp_timestamp,
95 rtc::ArrayView<const int16_t> audio,
96 rtc::Buffer* encoded) {
97 primary_encoded_.Clear();
98 EncodedInfo info =
99 speech_encoder_->Encode(rtp_timestamp, audio, &primary_encoded_);
100 RTC_CHECK(info.redundant.empty()) << "Cannot use nested redundant encoders.";
101 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(primary_encoded_.size(), info.encoded_bytes);
102
103 if (info.encoded_bytes == 0 || info.encoded_bytes > kRedMaxPacketSize) {
104 return info;
105 }
106 RTC_DCHECK_GT(max_packet_length_, info.encoded_bytes);
107
108 size_t header_length_bytes = kRedLastHeaderLength;
109 size_t bytes_available = max_packet_length_ - info.encoded_bytes;
110 auto it = redundant_encodings_.begin();
111
112 // Determine how much redundancy we can fit into our packet by
113 // iterating forward.
114 for (; it != redundant_encodings_.end(); it++) {
115 if (bytes_available < kRedHeaderLength + it->first.encoded_bytes) {
116 break;
117 }
118 if (it->first.encoded_bytes == 0) {
119 break;
120 }
121 bytes_available -= kRedHeaderLength + it->first.encoded_bytes;
122 header_length_bytes += kRedHeaderLength;
123 }
124
125 // Allocate room for RFC 2198 header if there is redundant data.
126 // Otherwise this will send the primary payload type without
127 // wrapping in RED.
128 if (header_length_bytes == kRedLastHeaderLength) {
129 header_length_bytes = 0;
130 }
131 encoded->SetSize(header_length_bytes);
132
133 // Iterate backwards and append the data.
134 size_t header_offset = 0;
135 while (it-- != redundant_encodings_.begin()) {
136 encoded->AppendData(it->second);
137
138 const uint32_t timestamp_delta =
139 info.encoded_timestamp - it->first.encoded_timestamp;
140 encoded->data()[header_offset] = it->first.payload_type | 0x80;
141 rtc::SetBE16(static_cast<uint8_t*>(encoded->data()) + header_offset + 1,
142 (timestamp_delta << 2) | (it->first.encoded_bytes >> 8));
143 encoded->data()[header_offset + 3] = it->first.encoded_bytes & 0xff;
144 header_offset += kRedHeaderLength;
145 info.redundant.push_back(it->first);
146 }
147
148 // |info| will be implicitly cast to an EncodedInfoLeaf struct, effectively
149 // discarding the (empty) vector of redundant information. This is
150 // intentional.
151 if (header_length_bytes > 0) {
152 info.redundant.push_back(info);
153 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(info.speech,
154 info.redundant[info.redundant.size() - 1].speech);
155 }
156
157 encoded->AppendData(primary_encoded_);
158 if (header_length_bytes > 0) {
159 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(header_offset, header_length_bytes - 1);
160 encoded->data()[header_offset] = info.payload_type;
161 }
162
163 // Shift the redundant encodings.
164 it = redundant_encodings_.begin();
165 for (auto next = std::next(it); next != redundant_encodings_.end();
166 it++, next = std::next(it)) {
167 next->first = it->first;
168 next->second.SetData(it->second);
169 }
170 it = redundant_encodings_.begin();
171 it->first = info;
172 it->second.SetData(primary_encoded_);
173
174 // Update main EncodedInfo.
175 if (header_length_bytes > 0) {
176 info.payload_type = red_payload_type_;
177 }
178 info.encoded_bytes = encoded->size();
179 return info;
180}
181
182void AudioEncoderCopyRed::Reset() {
183 speech_encoder_->Reset();
184 auto number_of_redundant_encodings = redundant_encodings_.size();
185 redundant_encodings_.clear();
186 for (size_t i = 0; i < number_of_redundant_encodings; i++) {
187 std::pair<EncodedInfo, rtc::Buffer> redundant;
188 redundant.second.EnsureCapacity(kAudioMaxRtpPacketLen);
189 redundant_encodings_.push_front(std::move(redundant));
190 }
191}
